                            <comment id="12577659" author="bryanduxbury" created="Wed, 12 Mar 2008 00:40:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s a patch to add this functionality for 0.1. (Nearly the same patch would apply to trunk, but let&apos;s see if this works first.)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12577703" author="stack" created="Wed, 12 Mar 2008 04:45:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 on patch.  Falls into the debugging tools category &amp;#8211; will help prove/disprove IRC theory that WREs just happen to be the last of a set of retryes &amp;#8211; so fine to apply to 0.1 branch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12577705" author="stack" created="Wed, 12 Mar 2008 04:52:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I saw below running tests on patch:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;junit&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; Tests run: 1, Failures: 1, Errors: 0, Time elapsed: 72.628 sec&lt;br/&gt;
    &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;junit&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; Test org.apache.hadoop.hbase.TestEmptyMetaInfo FAILED&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Do you see same?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12577714" author="bryanduxbury" created="Wed, 12 Mar 2008 05:21:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Don&apos;t see that failure in my test suite because the TestEmptyMetaInfo test doesn&apos;t exist yet. &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-27&quot; title=&quot;[hbase] hregioninfo cell empty in meta table&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-27&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-27&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; hasn&apos;t been applied, right?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12577717" author="stack" created="Wed, 12 Mar 2008 05:42:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Right.  My test bed was polluted w/ &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-27&quot; title=&quot;[hbase] hregioninfo cell empty in meta table&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-27&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-27&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12577931" author="bryanduxbury" created="Wed, 12 Mar 2008 17:12:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s the same thing but for trunk.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12577932" author="bryanduxbury" created="Wed, 12 Mar 2008 17:13:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Please review.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12577933" author="jimk" created="Wed, 12 Mar 2008 17:14:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That is really odd that TestEmptyMetaInfo should fail. Basically what it does is open the META table, stick in a bunch of rows that don&apos;t have info:regioninfo in them and wait for the master to clean them up.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12577957" author="bryanduxbury" created="Wed, 12 Mar 2008 18:05:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I ran TestEmptyMetaInfo against this patch now that it&apos;s committed, and it works fine.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12579086" author="bryanduxbury" created="Sat, 15 Mar 2008 21:27:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I just committed this to 0.1 and trunk.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
